<div class="calcpad-output">
 <!-- Stresses and settlement in an elastic half-space under a trapezoidal surface pressure on a rectangular footprint, obtained by numerical integration of the Boussinesq point-load kernel for $\sigma_z$, $\tau_{xz}$ and $\tau_{yz}$. -->
 <p>(by integration of the Boussinesq formula)</p>
 <p>
  Dimensions of loaded area -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>a</var>
   = 2
   <i>m</i>
  </span>
  ,
  <span class="eq">
   <var>b</var>
   = 3
   <i>m</i>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Surface load -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>p</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   ;
   <var>y</var>
   )  = 100
   <i>kPa</i>
   ·
   <span class="b1">(</span>
   1 +
   <span class="dvc">
    <var>x</var>
    <span class="dvl">
    </span>
    <var>a</var>
   </span>
   <span class="b1">)</span>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Elastic modulus -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>E</var>
   <sub>0</sub>
   = 20
   <i>MPa</i>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Poisson ratio -
  <span class="eq">
   <var>ν</var>
   = 0.3
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  <strong>Stress equations</strong>
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>R</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   ;
   <var>y</var>
   ;
   <var>z</var>
   )  =
   <span class="o0">
    <span class="r">√</span>
    <var>x</var>
    <sup>2</sup>
    +
    <var>y</var>
    <sup>2</sup>
    +
    <var>z</var>
    <sup>2</sup>
   </span>
  </span>
 </p>
 <p>
  Vertical -
